ease, you say things like =E2=80=9Cthis is a good company that will make a =
lot of money for shareholders.=E2=80=9D Alongside the announcement you will=
 typically file an investor presentation describing the key points of the c=
ompany and the deal; this will often contain the optimistic projections of =
future revenue for which SPACs are infamous. You=E2=80=99ll do an investor =
call, often the same morning you announce the deal, where the enthusiastic =
SPAC sponsor and the enthusiastic company management will talk about why it=
=E2=80=99s such a great investment opportunity. You might do one-on-one cal=
ls with key shareholders to address any of their concerns. The goal is to g=
et the retail investors and hedge funds who hold the stock to want to keep =
holding it, or to get other investors who like the company to buy the stock=
 when the hedge funds flip it, so that ultimately the stock is in the hands=
 of people who think it is worth more than $10 and will hold onto the stock=
 rather than ask for their money back.That=C2=A0is what you do if you have =
a company that you think will make money. Even if you have a pre-product, p=
re-revenue company, you explain to investors how it one day will=C2=A0make =
money. And if you have a company that=C2=A0won=E2=80=99t=C2=A0make money =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0if you know it won=E2=80=99t make money but you just wanted =
to play the SPAC game =E2=80=94=C2=A0then you also do this. You make stuff =
up. You slap together some optimistic projections, you=C2=A0roll some truck=
s down some hills, you get out there and you sell your deal so you can get =
your money.Unless you=E2=80=99re the Donald Trump SPAC, in which case, who =
cares.=C2=A0Anything you say to market the deal is going to be ridiculous, =
and people are going to buy it without marketing, so, whatever, it=E2=80=99=
s fine. Last Wednesday, a SPAC called Digital World Acquisition Corp.=C2=A0=
announced a merger with Donald Trump=E2=80=99s embryonic =E2=80=9CTrump Med=
ia & Technology Group.=E2=80=9D There is=C2=A0a press release, with a Trump=
y quote from Trump and a vague quote from DWAC chief executive officer Patr=
ick Orlando. There is no investor presentation for the deal, though there i=
s a rudimentary company overview deck=C2=A0on TMTG=E2=80=99s website; as we=
  discussed on Thursday, it has no dollar figures at all.Since the announce=
ment there have been a lot of news stories about, you know,  the stock goin=
g up, or about people on Reddit buying it, or about TMTG=E2=80=99s alleged =
social media site being an illegal clone=C2=A0of Mastodon. But there has no=
t been any news=C2=A0from the company. There have been no follow-up filings=
 or presentations. Trump and Orlando have not done a joint investor call la=
ying out their business plans and describing the capital structure of the n=
ew company. I=E2=80=99m not sure I have ever seen a=C2=A0secretive=C2=A0SPA=
C merger announcement before.=C2=A0Eventually this will have to change. Tru=
mp doesn=E2=80=99t ever need to=C2=A0launch a working social media service=
=C2=A0to get his $293 million from DWAC, but he will need to file a prospec=
tus with the Securities and Exchange Commission describing the business and=
 the capital structure and including=C2=A0historical financial statements. =
Also the prospectus will include a =E2=80=9CBackground of the Transaction=
=E2=80=9D section explaining how TMTG was founded and how it came to do a m=
erger with DWAC. I cannot tell you how excited I am to read this prospectus=
. I have read some good comedy SEC filings in my time, but my comedic expec=
tations for this one are absolutely sky-high. I assume a lot of plaintiffs'=
 lawyers are also very excited to read it for reasons of their own.Anyway, =
while Trump was conspicuously not marketing this deal to hedge funds, the h=
edge funds  were dumping their stock in an unusual mix of horror and glee a=
nd uproarious laughter:Saba Capital Management quickly sold its entire stak=
e of unrestricted stock in blank-check company Digital World Acquisition Co=
rp. on Thursday after discovering it planned to merge with former President=
 Donald Trump=E2=80=99s new media venture.=E2=80=9CI knew that for Saba the=
 right thing was to sell our entire stake of unrestricted shares, which we =
have now done,=E2=80=9D founder Boaz Weinstein said in an e-mailed statemen=
t. =E2=80=9CMany investors are grappling with hard questions about how to i=
